reviewText: First, Superman and Batman "Public Enemies" was in my opinion a very good story and an excellent movie that was very fast paced and also very entertaining.  The animation on this is fantastic, the voice talents are excellent as well. But even better than "Public Enemies", is "Apocalypse." I bought this on blu ray and this is one of my favorite movies, not just animated but any movie.  Awesome story, lots of action and excitement and really shows Batman and Superman working as a great team.  Supergirl makes her debut in this story and gives you a good look at her super powers and how she could be a force for good or evil.  Without giving away any story details, I will just say, if you are a Superman, Batman, or just a comic fan, I have a feeling you will love this movie and will not regret owning this dvd.  Well worth the money and the time to watch again and again.
summary: Great animated stories for any comic fan

reviewText: Superman and Batman are in a buddy movie. They have a strained friendship. They are both outcasts. Bryce Wayne's true identity is Batman, and Superman's true identity is Clark Kent. They have identities that they must maintain. Each man understands the sacrifices of being a superhero. This movie identifies and explains that special friendship.
